<section id="defs">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="kicker">Definitions</div>
    <h2>Words mean things here</h2>
    <div class="defs">
      <div class="def"><b>Operating</b><span>First verified megawatt delivered to compute load. Announcements, ribbon cuttings, and "energized" press releases don't qualify.</span></div>
      <div class="def"><b>Permitted</b><span>Air or siting permit issued — not applied for, not "expected." Appeals and violations are flagged, not hidden.</span></div>
      <div class="def"><b>Behind the meter</b><span>Generation serving on-site load without passing through a utility meter. Utility-built single-customer plants are tracked separately.</span></div>
      <div class="def"><b>Time to power</b><span>Months from first air-permit filing to first verified megawatt. Negative when operation preceded the permit.</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
